1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:06,798
AI coding tools forget the decisions a project already made, or make you resend far too much context.

2
00:00:06,798 --> 00:00:11,823
Qorx Zero gives that memory one clear home: your device.

3
00:00:11,823 --> 00:00:13,354
The promise is simple.

4
00:00:13,354 --> 00:00:14,719
Keep the context.

5
00:00:14,719 --> 00:00:15,892
Send the proof.

6
00:00:15,892 --> 00:00:21,250
These project decisions live in IndexedDB and survive browser sessions.

7
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:27,091
Each record carries importance, tags, a source hash, and an optional expiry.

8
00:00:27,091 --> 00:00:29,923
Nothing here is hidden behind a black box.

9
00:00:29,923 --> 00:00:37,640
When I ask what must ship before analytics, Qorx ranks the local records and selects only the one that supports the answer.

10
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:46,339
The proof desk shows the score, the matched terms, the source hash, the character budget, and the exact frame that can leave the device.

11
00:00:46,339 --> 00:00:50,918
If I ask for a production database password, there is no matching proof.

12
00:00:50,918 --> 00:00:54,693
Qorx sends nothing and refuses to invent an answer.

13
00:00:54,693 --> 00:00:56,772
No proof means no claim.

14
00:00:56,772 --> 00:00:59,426
Forgetting is just as visible.

15
00:00:59,426 --> 00:01:01,849
One tap deletes the video decision.

16
00:01:01,849 --> 00:01:04,668
Asking again confirms it cannot return.

17
00:01:04,668 --> 00:01:08,341
Expired records are also removed before recall.

18
00:01:08,341 --> 00:01:10,089
The full store stays local.

19
00:01:10,089 --> 00:01:19,681
A deterministic ranker combines relevance, importance, and recency, then caps the frame at five records and sixteen hundred characters.

20
00:01:19,681 --> 00:01:30,663
The server adapter uses the OpenAI Responses API with GPT-5.6 Terra, low reasoning, low verbosity, and storage disabled.

21
00:01:30,663 --> 00:01:37,895
GPT-5.6 receives the question and the visible proof frame, not the whole memory store.

22
00:01:37,895 --> 00:01:49,068
Codex with GPT-5.6 helped plan the clean-room boundary, build the app, write the tests, review the provider request, and prepare this public repository.

23
00:01:49,068 --> 00:01:52,857
The proprietary Qorx internals remain outside it.

24
00:01:52,857 --> 00:01:54,043
Qorx Zero.

25
00:01:54,043 --> 00:01:55,408
Keep the context.

26
00:01:55,408 --> 00:01:56,594
Send the proof.
